  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When  i recover my account on android, after i enetered passphrase and password and tapped `Sign In` - this `Sign In` button is shown for several seconds (not less then 3) so I am able to multitap it and this produces bugs https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4105 and https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4126\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen i tap `Sign In` i want the screen to be changed to `Signing you in` and sign in button is no longer available (same as on iOS). \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSign in button is available for multitap \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/39696760-61ad5e28-51f7-11e8-953f-62db204e3e3f.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\ndescribed in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4105 and https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4126\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly 367\r\n* Operating System:Android",
